<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Principal_values_in_the_com=
plex_plane">Principal values in the complex plane</h2><span class=3D"mw-edi=
tsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DInverse_hyperbolic_functions&amp;acti=
on=3Dedit&amp;section=3D10" title=3D"Edit section: Principal values in the =
complex plane"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">=
]</span></span></div>
<p>As <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Functions_of_a_complex_varia=
ble" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Functions of a complex variable">functi=
ons of a complex variable</a>, inverse hyperbolic functions are <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multivalued_function" title=3D"Multivalued fu=
nction">multivalued functions</a> that are <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Analytic_function" title=3D"Analytic function">analytic</a> except=
 at a finite number of points. For such a function, it is common to define =
a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Principal_value" title=3D"Princi=
pal value">principal value</a>, which is a single valued analytic function =
which coincides with one specific branch of the multivalued function, over =
a domain consisting of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complex=
_plane" title=3D"Complex plane">complex plane</a> in which a finite number =
of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arc_(geometry)" class=3D"mw-red=
irect" title=3D"Arc (geometry)">arcs</a> (usually <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Half_line" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Half line">half l=
ines</a> or <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Line_segment" title=3D=
"Line segment">line segments</a>) have been removed. These arcs are called =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Branch_cut" class=3D"mw-redirect" =
title=3D"Branch cut">branch cuts</a>. The principal value of the multifunct=
ion is chosen at a particular point and values elsewhere in the domain of d=
efinition are defined to agree with those found by <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Analytic_continuation" title=3D"Analytic continuation">ana=
lytic continuation</a>.
</p><p>For example, for the square root, the principal value is defined as =
the square root that has a positive <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Real_part" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Real part">real part</a>. This =
defines a single valued analytic function, which is defined everywhere, exc=
ept for non-positive real values of the variables (where the two square roo=
ts have a zero real part). This principal value of the square root function=
 is denoted <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span =
class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: non=
e;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\display=
style {\sqrt {x}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <msqrt>
            <mi>x</mi>
          </msqrt>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\sqrt {x}}}<=
/annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/d62b24be305beff66cba9bfbcc01a362ba390f44" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.005ex; width:3.266ex; height:3.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\s=
qrt {x}}}"></span> in what follows. Similarly, the principal value of the l=
ogarithm, denoted <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline">=
<span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"displa=
y: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \operatorname {Log} }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>Log</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \operatorname=
 {Log} }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/17ca0f245cc63bd68b10b5e95e686e8893e257fc" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:3.778ex; height:2.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \op=
eratorname {Log} }"></span> in what follows, is defined as the value for wh=
ich the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imaginary_part" class=3D"m=
w-redirect" title=3D"Imaginary part">imaginary part</a> has the smallest ab=
solute value. It is defined everywhere except for non-positive real values =
of the variable, for which two different values of the logarithm reach the =
minimum.
</p><p>For all inverse hyperbolic functions, the principal value may be def=
ined in terms of principal values of the square root and the logarithm func=
tion. However, in some cases, the formulas of <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Inverse_hyperbolic_functions#Definitions_in_terms_of_logarithms=
">=C2=A7&nbsp;Definitions in terms of logarithms</a> do not give a correct =
principal value, as giving a domain of definition which is too small and, i=
n one case <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Connected_space" title=
=3D"Connected space">non-connected</a>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Principal_value_of_the_inve=
rse_hyperbolic_sine">Principal value of the inverse hyperbolic sine</h3><sp=
an class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span>=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DInverse_hyperbolic_=
functions&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D11" title=3D"Edit section: Princi=
pal value of the inverse hyperbolic sine"><span>edit</span></a><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The principal value of the inverse hyperbolic sine is given by
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \operatorname {arsinh} z=3D\operatorname {Log} (z+{\sqrt {z^{2}=
+1}}\,)\,.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>arsinh</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mi>z</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>Log</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>z</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <msqrt>
            <msup>
              <mi>z</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>2</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msup>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </msqrt>
        </mrow>
        <mspace width=3D"thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mspace width=3D"thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \operatorname=
 {arsinh} z=3D\operatorname {Log} (z+{\sqrt {z^{2}+1}}\,)\,.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/70fe784a60fa94125f4be3f47212cb32eb6cf70a" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.838ex; width:30.204ex; height:3.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
operatorname {arsinh} z=3D\operatorname {Log} (z+{\sqrt {z^{2}+1}}\,)\,.}">=
</span>
</p><p>The argument of the square root is a non-positive <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Real_number" title=3D"Real number">real number</a>, =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/If_and_only_if" title=3D"If and on=
ly if">if and only if</a> <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>z</i></span> belongs t=
o one of the intervals <span class=3D"texhtml">[<i>i</i>, +<i>i</i>=E2=88=
=9E)</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml">(=E2=88=92<i>i</i>=E2=88=9E, =E2=88=
=92<i>i</i>]</span> of the imaginary axis. If the argument of the logarithm=
 is real, then it is positive. Thus this formula defines a principal value =
for arsinh, with branch cuts <span class=3D"texhtml">[<i>i</i>, +<i>i</i>=
=E2=88=9E)</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml">(=E2=88=92<i>i</i>=E2=88=9E, =
=E2=88=92<i>i</i>]</span>. This is optimal, as the branch cuts must connect=
 the singular points <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>i</i></span> and <span clas=
s=3D"texhtml">=E2=88=92<i>i</i></span> to infinity.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Principal_value_of_the_inve=
rse_hyperbolic_cosine">Principal value of the inverse hyperbolic cosine</h3=
><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</s=
pan><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DInverse_hyperbo=
lic_functions&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D12" title=3D"Edit section: Pr=
incipal value of the inverse hyperbolic cosine"><span>edit</span></a><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The formula for the inverse hyperbolic cosine given in <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inverse_hyperbolic_functions#Inverse_hyperbolic_cos=
ine">=C2=A7&nbsp;Inverse hyperbolic cosine</a> is not convenient, since sim=
ilar to the principal values of the logarithm and the square root, the prin=
cipal value of arcosh would not be defined for imaginary <span class=3D"tex=
html"><i>z</i></span>. Thus the square root has to be factorized, leading t=
o
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \operatorname {arcosh} z=3D\operatorname {Log} (z+{\sqrt {z+1}}=
{\sqrt {z-1}}\,)\,.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>arcosh</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mi>z</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>Log</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>z</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <msqrt>
            <mi>z</mi>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </msqrt>
        </mrow>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <msqrt>
            <mi>z</mi>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </msqrt>
        </mrow>
        <mspace width=3D"thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mspace width=3D"thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \operatorname=
 {arcosh} z=3D\operatorname {Log} (z+{\sqrt {z+1}}{\sqrt {z-1}}\,)\,.}</ann=
otation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/f0b2f2bc9a59a61c50e76891cc1c73c175f990ee" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.838ex; width:36.042ex; height:3.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
operatorname {arcosh} z=3D\operatorname {Log} (z+{\sqrt {z+1}}{\sqrt {z-1}}=
\,)\,.}"></span>
</p><p>The principal values of the square roots are both defined, except if=
 <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>z</i></span> belongs to the real interval <span=
 class=3D"texhtml">(=E2=88=92=E2=88=9E, 1]</span>. If the argument of the l=
ogarithm is real, then <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>z</i></span> is real and =
has the same sign. Thus, the above formula defines a principal value of arc=
osh outside the real interval <span class=3D"texhtml">(=E2=88=92=E2=88=9E, =
1]</span>, which is thus the unique branch cut.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Principal_values_of_the_inv=
erse_hyperbolic_tangent_and_cotangent">Principal values of the inverse hype=
rbolic tangent and cotangent</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/i=
ndex.php?title=3DInverse_hyperbolic_functions&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=
=3D13" title=3D"Edit section: Principal values of the inverse hyperbolic ta=
