eratorname {arcsch} z=3D\operatorname {Log} \left({\frac {1}{z}}+{\sqrt {{\=
frac {1}{z^{2}}}+1}}\,\right).}"></span>
</p><p>It is defined except when the arguments of the logarithm and the squ=
are root are non-positive real numbers. The principal value of the square r=
oot is thus defined outside the interval <span class=3D"texhtml">[=E2=88=92=
<i>i</i>, <i>i</i>]</span> of the imaginary line. If the argument of the lo=
garithm is real, then <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>z</i></span> is a non-zero=
 real number, and this implies that the argument of the logarithm is positi=
ve.
</p><p>Thus, the principal value is defined by the above formula outside th=
e <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Branch_cut" class=3D"mw-redirect=
" title=3D"Branch cut">branch cut</a>, consisting of the interval <span cla=
ss=3D"texhtml">[=E2=88=92<i>i</i>, <i>i</i>]</span> of the imaginary line.
</p><p>(At <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>z</i> =3D 0</span>, there is a singul=
ar point that is included in the branch cut.)
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Principal_value_of_the_inve=
