</p><p>If the argument of a square root is real, then <span class=3D"texhtm=
l"><i>z</i></span> is real, and it follows that both principal values of sq=
uare roots are defined, except if <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>z</i></span> i=
s real and belongs to one of the intervals <span class=3D"texhtml">(=E2=88=
=92=E2=88=9E, 0]</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml">[1, +=E2=88=9E)</span>.=
 If the argument of the logarithm is real and negative, then <span class=3D=
"texhtml"><i>z</i></span> is also real and negative. It follows that the pr=
incipal value of arsech is well defined, by the above formula outside two <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Branch_cut" class=3D"mw-redirect" t=
itle=3D"Branch cut">branch cuts</a>, the real intervals <span class=3D"texh=
tml">(=E2=88=92=E2=88=9E, 0]</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml">[1, +=E2=88=
=9E)</span>.
</p><p>For <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>z</i> =3D 0</span>, there is a singul=
ar point that is included in one of the branch cuts.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Graphical_representation">G=
raphical representation</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"m=
w-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.=
php?title=3DInverse_hyperbolic_functions&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D16=
" title=3D"Edit section: Graphical representation"><span>edit</span></a><sp=
an class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In the following graphical representation of the principal values of the=
 inverse hyperbolic functions, the branch cuts appear as discontinuities of=
 the color. The fact that the whole branch cuts appear as discontinuities, =
shows that these principal values may not be extended into analytic functio=
ns defined over larger domains. In other words, the above defined <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Branch_cut" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Branch cut">branch cuts</a> are minimal.
</p>
